{"word":"γνωρίζω","slug":"γνωρίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γνωρίζω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γιγνώσκω'><el>γιγνώσκω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make known, point out, explain</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to become known</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to make known</i>, <el>τινά τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to gain knowledge of, discover that</i> a thing is, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to be acquainted with, make acquaintance with</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}